sudo -> used to give superuser root privileges

sh -> Shebang 
bash -> borne again shell
zsh -> zee shell

/etc/passwd -> user data
/etc/shadow -> user password hashes
/etc/group -> groups  

kali hashes 

-> MD5

Windows hashes

C:\Windows\System32\config\SAM

-> NTLM

adduser kali // creates user

useradd kali // Create user with specific attributes

useradd -m kalu -s /bin/zsh -p 123 -u 2000

-m -> home directory
-s -> shell
-p -> password
-u -> user id

deluser Username   //deletes a user

userdel -r Username  //Deletes user along with all files related to it

*Making a user Superuser*

cat /etc/group | grep sudo

sudo usermod -a -G sudo UserName

-a -> add 
-G -> To Group


addgroup helmet

sudo usermod -aG helmet UserName
